Thank you for the report.

It has wrong default in bin/named/config.c, line 75. We did some directory customizations in default config file. But I think in this case, I would patch default inside binary.

Anyway, it has easy workaround, just specify correct geoip-directory in options:

options {
  # ...
  geoip-directory "/usr/share/GeoIP";
  # ...
};

The test [1] case does not update the crypto policy to FIPS. named-pkcs11 fails to start when the crypto policy is configured to FIPS mode and named.conf includes the bind configuration snippet from the crypto policy:

# update-crypto-policies --show
FIPS
# cat /etc/named.conf
options {
        ...
        include "/etc/crypto-policies/back-ends/bind.config";
};
